transmitMessage

public void transmitMessage(java.lang.String message)
/**

Transmits a message to the server. After the message has been sent, an additional newline character ('\n') is sent.

If an error occurs during the transmission, the client is disconnected. If the client is already disconnected when the method is called, no action is taken and the transmission request is silently ignored.

Parameters:
message - the message to send to the server.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - thrown if an I/O exception occurs.
